author: AccessWDUN Staff
title: Rabun County stomps Oglethorpe County to set up Union showdown
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 7: Region title, playoff races take shape after big night VIDEO: Brown, Lanier defense spark Longhorns to tough win over GHS 
LEXINGTON — Rabun County exploded to a 47-0 first half lead and cruised down the stretch, as the Wildcats hammered Oglethorpe County 60-12 on Friday in Lexington. 
Rabun County quarterback Bailey Fisher completed 14 of 19 passes for 299 yards and four touchdowns and also ran for a score to help lead the onslaught. 
The Wildcats (6-1, 3-0 Region 8-AA) also shut down the Patriots, allowing just 104 total yards. 
Rabun County now moves on to next week's top 10, Region 8-AA showdown with rival Union County in Tiger. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Rabun County football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
